  "title" : "springboot otlp telemetry turn off",
  "body" : "<p>I am using micrometer based otlp for enabling opentelemetry in springboot.</p>\n<pre><code>implementation 'io.micrometer:micrometer-tracing-bridge-otel'\nimplementation 'io.opentelemetry:opentelemetry-exporter-otlp'\n</code></pre>\n<p>I am looking for an option to turn opentelemetry off without removing these dependencies and/or other settings. I have tried all the below options in both configmaps as well as application.yaml but still end up with some traces being sent:</p>\n<p>configmap changes:</p>\n<p>OTEL_SDK_DISABLED: &quot;true&quot;\nOTEL_JAVAAGENT_ENABLED: &quot;false&quot;</p>\n<p>application.yaml chnges:</p>\n<p>management:\ntracing:\nenabled: false\nsampling:\nprobability: 0</p>\n<p>But still getting this error in the logs. The jaeger collection is not up but i don't expect any traces to be sent from the server.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>SEVERE: Failed to export spans. The request could not be executed. Full error message: jaeger-collector.default: Name does not resolve</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Any other settings to be placed?</p>\n"
}